derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: from Old French panier, from Latin panarium 'bread basket', from panis 'bread'

entry.tran: （自行车或摩托车后轮两侧的）挂包，挂篮，挂篓
entry.def: A pannier is one of two bags or boxes for carrying things in, which are fixed on each side of the back wheel of a bicycle or motorbike.

entry.tran: （通常挂在驮兽两侧的）驮篮，驮篓，驮包
entry.def: A pannier is a large basket or bag, usually one of two that are put over an animal and used for carrying loads.

means.word_mean: 1. a large wicker basket (usually one of a pair)
2. set of small hoops used to add fullness over the hips
